For this project I used PostgreSQL database.

I created 3 main tables:

## 1. Users
This table stores all users of the system.
Roles:
* Admin
* Manager
* Agent

Important fields:
* id
* name
* email
* password
* role

Email is unique for every user.

## 2. Leads
This table stores lead information.
Fields:
* name
* email
* phone
* source
* status
* assigned_to
* notes

A lead can be assigned to an agent.

## 3. Activity Logs
This table stores actions performed on leads.
Examples:
* Lead Created
* Lead Updated
* Lead Assigned
* Status Changed

This helps track changes in the system.

## Relationships

One user can have many leads.

One lead can have many activity logs.

Users (1) ---> Leads (Many)

Leads (1) ---> Activity Logs (Many)

## Why I Chose This Design

* Easy to understand
* Avoids duplicate data
* Supports future features
* Maintains relationship between users and leads
